Module-CheckDeps

Module::CheckDeps parses Perl code, and returns which used modules are
not yet installed.

In comparison to similar modules, such as Module::ScanDeps,
Module::CheckDeps is much more basic and simpler, but also faster.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Module::CheckDeps

You can also look for information at:

    Homepage homepage
        http://alexlog.co.cc/projects/module-checkdeps

    Git repository
        http://github.com/AlexBio/Module-CheckDeps

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Module-CheckDeps

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Module-CheckDeps

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Module-CheckDeps

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Module-CheckDeps/


